INSERT INTO `calendar_events` VALUES (1,'New Years Eve','Count down the new year at The Source. With New Year\'s specials from many of our tenants and a Cocktails and Caviar event hosted at Caprock Farm Bar\'s central bar, you\'ll be starting out your 2014 right.','The Source','2013-12-31 00:00:00','2014-01-01 00:00:00',0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),(2,'Morning Shift','<p>Beginning on Monday, January 13th, The Source will open every day at 8am with cold-pressed juice from CapRock, espresso and full-immersion brews from Boxcar Coffee, and croissants, morning buns, and butter cakes from Babettes. Not to mention free wi-fi and plenty of seating. Perfect for creative morning groups, early meetings, or just getting work done all while surrounded by some of the best artisans in town.</p>','The Source','2014-01-13 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2013-12-31 20:29:42','2014-01-04 04:10:51'),(3,'Deux Guitares','<p>Every Friday night from 7pm till 10pm, CapRock hosts Deux Guitares, a guitar duo playing Django Reinhardt-style gypsy jazz.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://deuxguitares.bandcamp.com/album/deux-guitares\">http://deuxguitares.bandcamp.com/album/deux-guitares</a></p>','CapRock','2014-01-03 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2013-12-31 20:30:20','2014-01-02 17:21:43'),(4,'Elise Wiggins Cooking Class ','Mondo Food, partnering with CapRock, hosts Executive Chef Elise Wiggins of Panzano who will be offering a cooking class at the CapRock Farm Bar on January 18th from 2-3pm. She will be demonstrating how to make hand rolled Gargenelli Pasta with Amatriciana Sauce.\r\n \r\nGuests can RSVP at events@mondofood.com ','Mondo Market & CapRock','2014-01-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2013-12-31 23:16:02','2013-12-31 23:17:15'),(5,'RiNo Social','<p>Please save the date on your calendar for the next RiNo Social! <strong>Wednesday, January 29th from 5-7pm.</strong> This event will be hosted by our<strong> <em>RiNo Urban Improvement Committee</em></strong> and will focus on informing our group on all the amazing things happening in the area and how you can get involved.<strong>It\'s a creative business meet up!</strong> Artists, designers, techies, architects, developers, brewers, innovators, winemakers, movers, shakers, foodies and other small businesses are invited!</p><p>More details to come! Stop in and connect with your community. Learn about membership and it\'s benefits. The social will be at <strong>Cap Rock, located at The Source, 3350 Brighton Blvd.</strong></p>','CapRock','2014-01-29 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-01-09 21:42:28','2014-01-09 21:42:28'),(6,'DJ Dan Grund ','<p>Come out to Caprock Farm Bar this Friday from 8-11pm for live music by DJ Dan Grund and $8 old fashions and gin martinis. View the flyer<a href=\"http://thesourcedenver.tumblr.com/post/73424858330/get-your-dance-on-this-friday-at-the-caprock-farm\"> here.</a> </p>','Caprock Farm Bar','2014-01-17 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-01-15 18:14:30','2014-01-15 18:14:30'),(7,'Superbowl Tailgate Brunch','<p>For Superbowl Sunday at Comida will be rolling out a Tailgate Brunch Party from 9am to 3pm. Expect awesome Super Bowl drink specials. You can view the full menu&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.eatcomida.com/cantina-menu/brunch-menu/\">here</a>.&nbsp;</p>','Comida','2014-02-02 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-01-21 19:04:22','2014-01-21 19:04:22'),(8,' Comida Celebrates Valentine’s Day Weekend','<p>In addition to Comida\'s usual fun menu we have a&nbsp;Wild mushroom lobster tamales and raw oyster shooters along with some drink&nbsp;special loving for&nbsp;Valentine’s Day.</p>','Comida','2014-02-13 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-01-29 16:28:19','2014-01-29 16:28:19'),(9,'Olympics Opening Ceremony 6:30-10:00pm','<p>We\'ll be showing the Sochi Olympics opening ceremony in its entirety tonight!</p>','Common Area/CapRock','2014-02-07 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-07 20:52:03','2014-02-07 20:52:26'),(10,'Olympics Fri 2/7- Sun 2/23','<p>We\'ll be showing the Olympics at the Source every day on our 150\" screen.</p>','Common Area/ CapRock Farm Bar','2014-02-23 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-07 21:44:15','2014-02-07 21:44:51'),(11,'The Dreamland Series 9am-6pm','<p><a href=\"http://dreamlandseries-com.securec43.ezhostingserver.com/?p=166\">The Dreamland Series</a> is bringing its latest set design entitled ‘star gazing” to Denver and will be setting up shop at The Source! As always reservations are required and spots are limited. You can sign up at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://info@dreamlandseries.com\">info@dreamlandseries.com</a> and as always since space is so limited full payment is required prior to your session. The cost is $350 and includes $150 in photo credits, set design, props, and wardrobe. Payment can be made&nbsp;<a href=\"http://propx.co/the-dreamland-series/p/O3TF640Y\">here</a>. If The Dreamland Series is able to fill this first shoot they\'d love to make the Source a regular studio space! So tell all your friends and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Dreamland-series/604704706260033\">like</a> The Dreamland Series on Facebook for all the latest and greatest.&nbsp;</p><p>From Dreamland:</p><p>\"<em>The Dreamland Series (<a href=\"http://www.dreamlandseries.com/\">www.dreamlandseries.com</a>) is a collaboration between photographer Sarah Hendsbee (<a href=\"http://www.sarahandbrad.com/\">www.sarahandbrad.com</a>) and stylist, Nicole Dominic-Pelletier (<a href=\"http://www.nicoledstylist.com/\">www.nicoledstylist.com</a>). Our goal is to create artistically designed photography for kids. Every other month we design a whole set including props & wardrobe inspired by a child\'s dreamland. We set up our studio twice a month for a limited amount of sessions. Each session is reserved fro 2 hours to allow plenty of time for wardrobe changes and for kids to fully explore the set. Afterwards we have a fun craft & play area set up for the kids to enjoy while the parents are able to immediately view the images and make product purchases with our assistance.</em></p><p><em>We are incredibly excited to bring our latest set entitled \"star gazing\" to a beautiful studio inside the Source Denver for one day only</em>!\"</p>','Jen Olson Photography (upstairs)','2014-02-15 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-11 01:51:32','2014-02-11 02:29:25'),(12,'Barley\'s Angels tasting 7pm','<p>Explore three tasters of sour beer from Crooked Stave Artisan Beer Project paired with cheeses from Mondo Market. Ladies only. Tickets can be purchased&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.barleysangelscolorado.com/#!eventsdenver/c21kz\">here</a>.</p>','Crooked Stave','2014-02-24 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-11 02:24:00','2014-02-11 02:24:00'),(13,'Doors Open Denver - 8am-11pm','<p>The 10th Anniversary of Doors OPEN Denver will be held on April 12th and 13th.  The Denver Architectural Foundation annually presents this free two-day event of tours in and around Denver’s most interesting buildings.  Headquarters for 2014 will be at 1801 California Street.</p><p>The 2014 theme Celebrating Neighborhood Architecture will feature sites and tours in the neighborhoods of Downtown, Capitol Hill, LoDo, Santa Fe, Park Hill, Five Points, Highlands, Hill Top, Uptown, Cherry Creek, The Mariposa District, Golden Triangle, Baker (South Broadway), RiNo, the Auraria Campus and others.</p><p>Expert tours of The Source will be available both days. Please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.doorsopendenver.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.doorsopendenver.org</a> for more information and to reserve your spot on a tour.</p>','The Source','2014-04-12 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-14 22:06:18','2014-02-14 22:06:18'),(14,'Doors Open Denver - 8am-11pm','<p>The 10th Anniversary of Doors OPEN Denver will be held on April 12th and 13th.  The Denver Architectural Foundation annually presents this free two-day event of tours in and around Denver’s most interesting buildings.  Headquarters for 2014 will be at 1801 California Street.</p><p>The 2014 theme Celebrating Neighborhood Architecture will feature sites and tours in the neighborhoods of Downtown, Capitol Hill, LoDo, Santa Fe, Park Hill, Five Points, Highlands, Hill Top, Uptown, Cherry Creek, The Mariposa District, Golden Triangle, Baker (South Broadway), RiNo, the Auraria Campus and others.</p>','The Source','2014-04-13 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-14 22:06:34','2014-02-14 22:06:34'),(15,'New Works by Caleb Hahne - 6pm-10pm','<p><strong>A BROKEN FRAME - New Works by <wbr>Caleb Hahne</strong></p><p>Super Ordinary is pleased to present A Broken From - New Works by Caleb R. Hahne. Please join us for the Opening Reception on Second Saturday, March 8th from 6p-10p at Super Ordinary located at The Source. Artist will be in attendance. <br><br>Artist Statement<br><br>My practice involves the utilization of technology and traditional techniques by confronting the allure of a blooming cyber media. Intrigued by the concept of remixing, I integrate traditional means of art making with a contemporary approach by digitally collaging appropriated imagery from textbooks and magazines and then drawing the new compositions. My current body of work involves the material engagement of found paper and objects, graphite, ballpoint pen, oil paint, and acetone along with other mixed medias.&nbsp;</p><p>For more information about Caleb please visit: <br><a href=\"http://www.calebhahne.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.calebhahne.com/</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.calebhahne.com/\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://theresaandersonart.com/caleb-hahne-showpen-residency/\" target=\"_blank\">http://theresaandersonart.com/caleb-hahne-showpen-residency/</a></p>','SVPER ORDINARY','2014-03-08 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-02-26 18:53:49','2014-02-28 00:37:22'),(16,'Slow Food Annual Meeting - 5:30pm-7:30pm','<p><strong>Please join us for the Slow Food Denver 2014 Annual Meeting</strong></p><p>Don\'t miss the chance to learn more about Slow Food Denver and meet others with similar interests and passions.  We\'ll gather in the common area at the Source, home of the new Slow Food Denver offices, for an open-house style celebration to mingle and learn about Slow Food Denver\'s work and plans for the future.  This is a great opportunity to learn more about opportunities to get involved.  We will provide light snacks and beverages.</p><p>For those who have attended in the past, this year\'s gathering will be less of us talking and more opportunity for you to socialize, learn and mingle. </p><p><strong>Join us in creating positive change in our food community!</strong></p><p>5:30 - 6:00 ~ Slowing down. . . socializing, eating, drinking</p><p>6:00 - 6:15 ~ Welcome</p><p>6:15 - 7:15 ~ Open house</p><p>7:15 - 7:30 ~ Closing remarks</p><p>Join Slow Food Denver on <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/slowfooddenver\">Facebook</a></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-03-10 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-04 18:13:35','2014-03-04 18:16:14'),(17,'Downslope Distilling Pop-Up - Shaken, Drafted & Punched - 11am-11pm','<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/DownslopeDistilling\">Downslope Distilling</a> is popping up a tasting room at The Source marketplace all this weekend (March 14-16) for <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/DSTILL.CO\">DSTILL</a>. Downslope\'s Anthony Giovanni steps behind the bar with a new menu each night curated with McLain Hedges of <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/properpour\">The Proper Pour</a>.</p><p><br>Closing out the final days of DSTILL, we are keeping the vibe alive with the serious celebration of American Craft Spirits.<br><br>Stop in after work and pick up a bottle of whiskey before heading home or start your night with cocktails at the bar.<br><br>Shaken on Friday, Drafted on Saturday, and Punches on Sunday. Menus have been posted with more on the way.<br><br>Friday | Shaken Cocktails<br>Saturday | Cocktails on Draft<br>Sunday | Punch!<br><br>We will be providing pop-up classes as the bar fills up through the day. Classes on spirits, history of gin (Ould Tom), rums, whiskies, and vodkas of all types.<br><br>Collaborators include <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/IndustryDenver\">Industry Denver</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/PresseryJuice\">Pressery</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TheRealDillCo\">The Real Dill</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/teakoetea\">Teakoe & Company</a>, and more.</p><p>Pressery Juicebar opens at 11 daily<img src=\"https://scontent-a-ord.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ash3/t1.0-9/1800354_10152334276928487_832739160_n.jpg\"></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-03-14 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-11 19:45:21','2014-03-13 00:25:08'),(18,'Green Drinks - 6pm-8pm','<p>Green drinks Denver provides an open forum to meet like-minded individuals interested in an environmentally conscious lifestyle. This informal, social networking event is centered around a featured GREEN topic and a common goal of balancing the environmental, economic and social aspects of sustainability.</p><p>Learn more&nbsp;<a href=\"https://milehighbiz.org/civicrm/event/info?reset=1&id=195\">here</a>.</p>','Crooked Stave','2014-03-27 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-13 00:24:58','2014-03-26 00:02:26'),(19,'Creative Mornings - 8:30am-10am','<p>The Source welcomes Creative Mornings! Creative Mornings takes place monthly, so check back here for info on upcoming lectures.</p><p>Click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://creativemornings.com/about\">HERE</a> to learn more about the Creative Mornings organization.</p><p>This month:</p><p>Come here Kellen Kurtz of Love146 talk about their organization and how they’re working to end child trafficking and exploitation.</p><p>Love146 uses unexpected and creative means to combats child trafficking and does extensive work to help restore survivors after abolition. Slavery is still one of the darkest stories on our planet. It is both a global and a local problem, but through Love146 the hope of abolition is made into a reality for many people across the globe.</p><p>Love146 believes in helping grow the movement of abolition while providing effective, thoughtful solutions. They believe in the power of Love and its ability to affect sustainable change. Love is the foundation of our motivation.</p><p>Coffee provided by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.boxcarcoffeeroasters.com\">Boxcar Coffee</a> @ The Source</p><p>Pastries provided by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.babettesbakery.com/\">Babettes</a> @ The Source</p><p><a href=\"http://creativemornings.com/cities/den\">http://creativemornings.com/cities/den</a></p>','Common Area','2014-04-11 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-19 21:12:28','2014-03-19 21:24:48'),(20,'Colorado Makers Spring Market - 11am-7pm','<p>details coming soon</p><p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/ColoradoMakers\">facebook.com/coloradomakers</a></p>','Common Area','2014-05-03 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-19 21:15:00','2014-03-19 22:01:32'),(22,'Dancing Pines Distillery Pop-Up','<p>Fri 3/21 - Sun 3/23</p><p><a href=\"http://www.dancingpinesdistillery.com/\">dancingpinesdistillery.com</a></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-03-21 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-19 22:11:42','2014-03-19 22:11:42'),(23,'Spring 44 Distillery Pop-Up','<p>Fri 3/28 - Sun 3/30</p><p><a href=\"http://spring44.com/home\">spring44.com</a></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-03-28 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-19 22:12:57','2014-03-19 22:13:50'),(24,'Peach Street Distillery Pop-Up','<p>Thurs 4/3 - Sat 4/4</p><p><a href=\"http://www.peachstreetdistillers.com/\">peachstreetdistillers.com</a></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-04-03 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-03-19 22:15:09','2014-03-19 22:15:09'),(25,'WORLD WHISKY DAY meets Bridges to Prosperity | 11am - 11pm','<p>It\'s world whisky day! Come down to the Common Area Bar to drink some delicious whisky drinks concocted by The Proper Pour to benefit the non-profit organization, Bridges to Prosperity. Come meet the Bridges team from 2:30 - 4:30!</p><p><a href=\"http://bridgestoprosperity.org/\">http://bridgestoprosperity.org/</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.theproperpour.com/\">http://www.theproperpour.com/</a></p>','Common Area Bar','2014-05-17 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-13 20:17:48','2014-05-14 20:47:42'),(26,'Brunch Bar | 10am - 2pm','<p>Nurse your hangovers with brunch style cocktails provided by The Proper Pour to benefit a non-profit organization, Bridges to Prosperity.&nbsp;</p><p>http://bridgestoprosperity.org/</p>','Common Bar Area','2014-05-18 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-13 20:52:03','2014-05-13 21:19:15'),(27,'Bridges to Prosperity and Tiki Drinks | Thursday and Friday 5pm - 11pm','<p>Come kick off the summer with Tiki inspired drinks provided by The Proper Pour to benefit a fabulous non-profit organization, Bridges to Prosperity!</p><p><a href=\"http://bridgestoprosperity.org/\">http://bridgestoprosperity.org/</a></p><p>http://www.theproperpour.com/</p>','Common Area Bar','2014-05-15 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-14 20:37:00','2014-05-14 20:37:00'),(28,'Bottle Rocket Launch Party!','<p>Join the Boxcar Coffee Roasters&nbsp;to help them celebrate the launch of their new cold brew, Bottlerocket, and the official grand opening of their new roastery at The Source!&nbsp;</p><p><br>Stop by on Saturday May 24th for snacks, drinks, coffee, music, latte art competition and late night dance party from 6pm-Late. <br><br>There will be door prizes, raffle giveaways and amazing prize packs for the winners of the latte art competition. <br><br>More details coming soon but for now be sure to save the date and follow along with #bottlerocketlaunch<br><br>See you there!</p>','Boxcar Coffee Roasters','2014-05-24 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-20 15:56:42','2014-05-20 15:56:42'),(29,'Denver B-Cycle Pop-up and Giro d\'Italia','<p>Join us in the common bar area for delightful drinks from The Proper Pour&nbsp;and viewing of the Giro d\'Italia all to benefit Denver B Cycle!</p><p><br>Friday | 5pm - 10pm<br>Saturday | 12pm - 10pm<br><br>We will be showing the Giro d\'Italia both days starting at 5pm!<br>See you there!</p><p><a href=\"http://www.theproperpour.com/\">http://www.theproperpour.com/</a></p><p>https://denver.bcycle.com/</p>','Common Area Bar','2014-05-30 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-28 23:44:41','2014-05-28 23:44:41'),(30,'Giro d\'Italia and Denver B-Cycle Pop-up','<p>Join us in the common bar area for delightful drinks from <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/properpour\">The Proper Pour</a>and viewing of the Giro d\'Italia all to benefit Denver B Cycle!</p><p><br>Friday | 5pm - 10pm<br>Saturday | 12pm - 10pm<br><br>We will be showing the Giro d\'Italia both days starting at 5pm!<br>See you there!</p><p><a href=\"https://denver.bcycle.com/\">https://denver.bcycle.com/</a></p><p>http://www.theproperpour.com/</p>','common area bar','2014-05-31 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-05-28 23:46:23','2014-05-28 23:46:23'),(31,'World Cup 2014 Kick-off Game','<p>We will be showing the first World Cup game of 2014 in the common area.&nbsp;</p><p>Game starts at 2pm!! BRAZIL vs. CROATIA</p><p>Check weekly and daily for schedules for all the games during the World Cup.</p>','Common Area','2014-06-12 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-05 20:01:18','2014-06-05 20:01:18'),(32,'Platte Forum meets Verboten Brewing |  Fri: 5pm-10pm  Sat: 12pm - 10pm','<p>Platte Forum, a local non-profit, will be hosting a pop-up event located in the common area bar. They are a fantastic organization that gives hope and direction to underserved youth who collaborate with master artists from around the world.</p><p>Verboten Brewing will be serving beer in the common area bar to benefit Platte Forum. Verboten Brewing is an award-winning brewery located in Loveland. Come try their delicious, unique beers for a good cause!</p><p>During the entire weekend we also have the privilege of viewing a thread art installation by the talented Claudia Mastobuono that will be in the space of the Source above the common area bar.</p><p><a href=\"http://platteforum.org/\">http://platteforum.org/</a></p><p>http://www.verbotenbrewing.com/</p><p><a href=\"http://claudiamastrobuono.com/home.html\">http://claudiamastrobuono.com/home.html</a></p>','Common Bar Area','2014-06-13 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-05 20:08:14','2014-06-05 20:10:37'),(33,'Caipirinhas and the World Cup','<p>It\'s World Cup time! What better way to kick off the World Cup in Brazil than drinking Caipirinhas and other delicious Cachaça Cocktails! Come try the tasty concoctions &nbsp;supplied by Novo Fogo and cheer on your favorite teams!</p><p>FRIDAY | 5pm - 10pm</p><p>SATURDAY | 12pm - 10pm</p><p>http://www.novofogo.com/</p>','Common Area Bar','2014-06-14 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-11 16:36:51','2014-06-11 16:36:51'),(34,'Slow Meat \"Resistance\" Film Screening | 6:30 - 9:30pm','<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Following the Slow Meat gathering, Slow Food Denver, Uji Films, Applegate, and Food and Water Watch will screen the new documentary <em>Resistance</em> in Denver, CO on June 22nd.  The doucmentary uses a blend of interviews, archival materials, animation, and vérité footage shot across the U.S. and other parts of the globe to showcase how the modern miracle of mass-produced antibiotics is reaching a potentially catastrophic scenario due to overuse and mismanagement.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table><p>Free Entry</p><p>Snacks Provided | Cash Bar</p>','Common Area','2014-06-22 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-17 16:26:58','2014-06-17 16:26:58'),(35,'Creative Mornings | 8:30am ','<p>Do you know how your shirt was made? Where the cotton was picked, the yarn spun, the fabric knitted, the pieces sewn together?</p><p>Most people don’t. It’s a part of our American heritage that’s been left behind, in favor of globalization, “new” labor markets, and a desire for low-cost, mass consumption.</p><p>Kristin Glenn wasn’t too sure where her clothes came from, either. In fact, she was a total shopaholic – until a round-the-world trip and a successful Kickstarter campaign launched her into the world of sustainable fashion. She’s spent the last four years researching the apparel industry, talking with professors, farmers, CEOs, and activists – all while building a sustainable fashion company.</p><p>In 2013, Glenn founded Seamly.co, a Colorado-based clothing company that focuses on versatile, multifunctional design. Seamly.co uses surplus fabrics (excess from mills and factories around the US) to create garments within a 40-mile radius of her Denver home.</p><p>At this month’s CreativeMornings session, she’ll be discussing her personal journey from fast fashion junkie to socially responsible business owner. It includes a backpacking trip in Asia, a factory in North Carolina, a garment that can be worn over 30 different ways, and the most successful fashion Kickstarter campaign of its time…</p><p>Here\'s the link to register:</p><p><a href=\"http://creativemornings.com/talks/kristin-glenn\">http://creativemornings.com/talks/kristin-glenn</a></p><p>Here\'s  a link to the chapter page:</p><p><a href=\"http://creativemornings.com/cities/den\">http://creativemornings.com/cities/den</a></p>','Common Area','2014-07-11 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-17 16:30:13','2014-07-01 19:15:24'),(36,'World Cup Weekend | 3 Chicks Bartending','<p>Join us from 5pm - 10pm in the common area bar to watch the World Cup and drink local beers, wines and hand-crafted cocktails from the crew at 3 Chicks Bartending!!</p>','Common Area Bar','2014-06-20 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'2014-06-18 17:42:08','2014-06-18 17:42:08'),(37,'3 Chicks Bartending | World Cup Weekend','<p>Come on down and watch the World Cup and sip on some drinks from the crew from 3 Chicks Bartending! They\'ll be 